Day 2 - Chapter 1
1) Primitive Data Types.
=> Python primitive data types are the most basic kinds of values you can store in variables: numbers, text, and true/false values.
=>The 4 main primitive data types you’ll use all the time are:​
i.int → integers (whole numbers),
ii.float → decimal numbers.
iii.str → strings (text). 
iv.bool → booleans (truth values).

Example:- 
age = 21          # int
height = 5.9      # float
name = "Azuma"    # str
is_student = True # bool

You can check the type using type():
print(type(age))       # lass 'int'>
print(type(height))    # lass 'float'>
print(type(name))      # lass 'str'>
print(type(is_student))# lass 'bool'>

